get.description: Result : a single number giving the elevation in meters according to aster gdem, ocean areas have been masked as "no data" and have been assigned a value of -9999

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

examples.application/xml:
<geonames>
<astergdem>192</astergdem>
<lat>50.01</lat>
<lng>10.2</lng>
</geonames>

get.description: Result: returns a list of GeoName records

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: number of rows returned, default is 200

parameters.name: hierarchy
parameters.description: this optional parameter allows to use other hiearchies then the default administrative hierarchy. So far only 'tourism' is implemented.

get.description: Result : returns a list of cities and placenames in the bounding box, ordered by relevancy (capital/population). Placenames close together are filterered out and only the larger name is included in the resulting list.

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: language of placenames and wikipedia urls (default = en)

parameters.name: east
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: west
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: north
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: south
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

examples.application/xml:
<geonames>
<geoname>
<toponymName>Mexico City</toponymName>
<name>Mexico City</name>
<lat>19.42847</lat>
<lng>-99.12766</lng>
<geonameId>3530597</geonameId>
<countryCode>MX</countryCode>
<countryName>Mexico</countryName>
<fcl>P</fcl>
<fcode>PPLC</fcode>
</geoname>
<geoname>
<toponymName>Manila</toponymName>
<name>City of Manila</name>

get.description: returns all features within the GeoName feature for the given geoNameId. It only returns contained features when a polygon boundary for the input feature is defined.

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description:
The iso country code of any given point.
Result : returns the iso country code for the given latitude/longitude
With the parameter type=xml this service returns an xml document with iso country code and country name. The optional parameter lang can be used to specify the language the country name should be in. JSON output is produced with type=JSON

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

examples.application/xml:
<geonames>
<country>
<countryCode>AT</countryCode>
<countryName>Austria</countryName>
<languages>de-AT,hr,hu,sl</languages>
<distance>0</distance>
</country>
</geonames>

get.description: Result : returns the closest populated place (feature class=P) for the lat/lng query as xml document. The unit of the distance element is 'km'.

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: language of returned 'name' element (the pseudo language code 'local' will return it in local language)

parameters.name: localCountry
parameters.description: in border areas this parameter will restrict the search on the local country,

parameters.name: cities
parameters.description: optional filter parameter with three possible values 'cities1000', 'cities5000','cities15000

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: verbosity of returned xml document, default = MEDIUM

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

<geonames>
<geoname>
<toponymName>Chrüzegg</toponymName>
<name>Chrüzegg</name>
<lat>47.2985</lat>
<lng>9.01488</lng>
<geonameId>7910950</geonameId>
<countryCode>CH</countryCode>
<countryName>Switzerland</countryName>
<fcl>P</fcl>
<fcode>PPLX</fcode>
<distance>1.1379</distance>
</geoname>
</geonames>

get.description: Result : returns a list of postalcodes and places for the lat/lng query as xml document. The result is sorted by distance. For Canada the FSA is returned (first 3 characters of full postal code)

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: the maximal number of rows in the document returned by the service.

get.description:
Finds the nearest streets for a given lat/lng pair.
Result: returns the nearest street segments for the given latitude/longitude

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description:
Finds the nearest street for a given lat/lng pair.
Result : returns the nearest street segments for the given latitude/longitude
Restriction : this webservice is only available for the US.

get.description:
This service comes in two flavors. You can either pass the lat/long or a postalcode/placename.
Result : returns a list of wikipedia entries as xml document

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: ISO language code of article text

parameters.name: summary
parameters.description: a short summary of the article text. Around 300 chars. The text is truncated at a full stop if one is available near char 300, otherwise at the end of a word.

parameters.name: countryCode
parameters.description: the ISO country code of the article

parameters.name: elevation
parameters.description: the elevation in metres (optional may be null), parsed from the article or reverse geocoded.

parameters.name: thumbnailImg
parameters.description: URL of a small thumbnail image (ca 100x75 px)

parameters.name: rank
parameters.description: indication of the popularity or relevancy of an article. The rank is an integer number from 1 for the least popular articles to 100 for the most popular articles. It is calculated from the number of links pointing to an article and the article length. The articles are more or less evenly distributed over the 100 ranks.

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

examples.application/xml:
<geonames>
<entry>
<lang>en</lang>
<title>Glärnisch</title>
<summary>
The Glärnisch is a mountain of the Glarus Alps, overlooking the valley of the Linth in the Swiss canton of Glarus. get.description:
Finds the nearest street and address for a given lat/lng pair.
Result : returns the nearest address for the given latitude/longitude, the street number is an 'educated guess' using an interpolation of street number at the end of a street segment.

The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

<geonames>
<address>
<street>Roble Ave</street>
<mtfcc>S1400</mtfcc>

<lng>-122.18032</lng>
<distance>0.04</distance>

<adminName2>San Mateo</adminName2>

</address>

get.description:
Finds the nearest street and the next crossing street for a given lat/lng pair.
Result : returns the nearest intersection for the given latitude/longitude

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

examples.application/xml:
<geonames>
<intersection>
<street1>Roble Avenue</street1>
<highway1>residential</highway1>
<street1Bearing>213</street1Bearing>
<street2>Curtis Street</street2>
<highway2>residential</highway2>
<street2Bearing>303</street2Bearing>
<lat>37.4506505</lat>
<lng>-122.1808293</lng>
<distance>0.08</distance>
</intersection>
</geonames>

get.description:
Webservice for the GeoNames full text search in xml and json format. 
Returns a list of postal codes and places for the placename/postalcode query as xml document 
For the US the first returned zip code is determined using zip code area shapes, the following zip codes are based on the centroid. For all other supported countries all returned postal codes are based on centroids.

parameters.name: postalcode_startsWith
parameters.description: the first characters or letters of a postal code

parameters.name: placename
parameters.description: all fields : placename,postal code, country, admin name (Important:urlencoded utf8)

parameters.name: placename_startsWith
parameters.description: the first characters of a place name

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: Default is all countries. string : country code, ISO-3166 (optional)

parameters.name: countryBias
parameters.description: records from the countryBias are listed first

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: the maximal number of rows in the document returned by the service. Default is 10

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description: the operator 'AND' searches for all terms in the placename parameter, the operator 'OR' searches for any term, default = AND

parameters.name: isReduced
parameters.description: default is 'false', when set to 'true' only the UK outer codes are returned. Attention: the default value on the commercial servers is currently set to 'true'. It will be changed later to 'false'.

parameters.name: east
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: west
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: north
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: south
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: verbosity of returned xml document, default = MEDIUM

200.description:

The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description: returns a RSS feed with latitude and longitude for each entry where the geonames search engine has found a relevant location. Already existant GeoRSS elements in the feed remain unchanged. There is an upper limit of 20 entries for performance reasons.

parameters.name: feedUrl
parameters.description: The url of the RSS feed to search locations for and to convert to GeoRSS. The feed has to be syntactically correct, i.e. wellformed xml and valid rss/atom.

parameters.name: feedLanguage
parameters.description: The language of the feed, this information is needed by the geonames search engine to find relevant locations. Default : No value = automatic language detection.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: The output RSS dialect of the conversion. Default : same RSS dialect as input feed.

parameters.name: geoRSS
parameters.description: The GeoRSS output encoding used for lat/lng. See www.georss.org for details. Default is w3cGeo.

parameters.name: addUngeocodedItems
parameters.description: Items that could not be geocoded are removed from the response document. Setting the parameter addUngeocodedItems=true will include the ungeocoded items in the response.

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: Restrict geocoding to a given country. This parameter may improve the results of the geocoder for feeds focusing on a single country.

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description: returns the names found for the searchterm as xml or json document, the search is using an AND operator

parameters.name: q
parameters.description: search over all attributes of a place : place name, country name, continent, admin codes,... (Important:urlencoded utf8)

parameters.name: name_startsWith
parameters.description: place name starts with given characters

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: the maximal number of rows in the document returned by the service. Default is 100, the maximal allowed value is 1000.

parameters.name: startRow
parameters.description: Used for paging results. If you want to get results 30 to 40, use startRow=30 and maxRows=10. Default is 0.

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: Default is all countries. The country parameter may occur more than once, example: country=FR&country=GP

parameters.name: countryBias
parameters.description: records from the countryBias are listed first

parameters.name: continentCode
parameters.description: restricts the search for toponym of the given continent.

parameters.name: featureClass
parameters.description: this parameter may occur more than once, example: featureClass=P&featureClass=A

parameters.name: featureCode
parameters.description: (default= all feature codes); this parameter may occur more than once, example: featureCode=PPLC&featureCode=PPLX

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description:
"place name and country name will be returned in the specified language. Default is English. 
Feature classes and codes are only available in English and Bulgarian. Any help in translating is welcome."

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: the format type of the returned document, default = xml

parameters.name: isNameRequired
parameters.description:
"At least one of the search term needs to be part of the place name. Example : A normal search for Berlin will return all places within the state of Berlin. If we only want to find places with 'Berlin' in the name we set the parameter isNameRequired to 'true'. 
The difference to the name_equals parameter is that this will allow searches for 'Berlin, Germany' as only one search term needs to be part of the name."

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: search for toponyms tagged with the specified tag

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description: default is 'AND', with the operator 'OR' not all search terms need to be matched by the response

parameters.name: charset
parameters.description: default is 'UTF8', defines the encoding used for the document returned by the web service.

parameters.name: fuzzy
parameters.description: default is '1', defines the fuzziness of the search terms. float between 0 and 1.

parameters.name: searchlang
parameters.description: in combination with the name parameter, the search will only consider names in the specified language. Used for instance to query for IATA airport codes.

parameters.name: orderby
parameters.description: in combination with the name_startsWith, if set to 'relevance' than the result is sorted by relevance.

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: verbosity of returned xml document, default = MEDIUM

parameters.name: east
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: west
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: north
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: south
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description: Result : returns the wikipedia entries within the bounding box as xml document

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: ISO language code of article text

parameters.name: summary
parameters.description: a short summary of the article text. Around 300 chars. The text is truncated at a full stop if one is available near char 300, otherwise at the end of a word.

parameters.name: countryCode
parameters.description: the ISO country code of the article

parameters.name: elevation
parameters.description: the elevation in metres (optional may be null), parsed from the article or reverse geocoded.

parameters.name: thumbnailImg
parameters.description: URL of a small thumbnail image (ca 100x75 px)

parameters.name: rank
parameters.description: indication of the popularity or relevancy of an article. The rank is an integer number from 1 for the least popular articles to 100 for the most popular articles. It is calculated from the number of links pointing to an article and the article length. The articles are more or less evenly distributed over the 100 ranks.

parameters.name: east
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: west
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: north
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: south
parameters.description: bounding box, only features within the box are returned

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.

get.description: Result : returns the wikipedia entries found for the searchterm as xml document

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: ISO language code of article text

parameters.name: summary
parameters.description: a short summary of the article text. Around 300 chars. The text is truncated at a full stop if one is available near char 300, otherwise at the end of a word.

parameters.name: countryCode
parameters.description: the ISO country code of the article

parameters.name: elevation
parameters.description: the elevation in metres (optional may be null), parsed from the article or reverse geocoded.

parameters.name: thumbnailImg
parameters.description: URL of a small thumbnail image (ca 100x75 px)

parameters.name: rank
parameters.description: indication of the popularity or relevancy of an article. The rank is an integer number from 1 for the least popular articles to 100 for the most popular articles. It is calculated from the number of links pointing to an article and the article length. The articles are more or less evenly distributed over the 100 ranks.

200.description:
If a request for a geonames web service encounters an error the following exception format will be used for the returned document. GeoNames supports two flavor of web services - JSON and XML. 
The exception message returned is either JSON or XML and consists of a status element with a numeric error code and a message string.
